div1.p: In the United States District Court, In and For the Western District of Washington, Northern Divison.
In the Matter of the Application of Chin Hing, for a Writ of Habeas Corpus. } No. 2827 Praecipe (for certified Copy of Citation)
To the Clerk of the Above entitled Court:
You will please issue one cerified copy of the Citation in the above entitled cause, and hand same to the Marshal for service.
div1.ab: John J Sullivan Attorney for Petitioner Chin Hing
div1.p: In the United States District Court, In and For the Western District of Washington, Northern Division.
In the Matter of the Application of Chin Hing, for a Writ of Habeas Corpus. } No. 2875. Praecipe (for Record)
To the Clerk of the Above entitled Court:

You will please prepare transcript of record in the above entitled cause on appeal, and file same in the Circuit Court of Appeals, omitting therefrom the briefs of both counsel, the Opinion of Justice Dealing, which was put n the filws only for the convenience of the court, and is not a part of the record, and the orginial petition, as a further amended petition was filed by leave of court, containing an allegaion of all facts relied upon. This will include an Opinion by Justice Morton, which you will find in an envelope attached to the record and made a part thereof. and Ex A except pages 8-9-31-32-33-35-36-37-38- 39-40-45-46-47-58.
div1.ab: John J Sullivan Attorney for Petitioner
div1.p: We waive the provisions of the Act approved Feburary 13, 1911, and direct that you forward typewritten transcript to the Circuit Court of Appeals for printing as provided under Rule 105 of this Court.
In and For the Western District of Washington, Northern Division.
In the Matter of the Application of Chin Hing, for a Writ of Habeas Corpus
Praecipe (for Certified Copy of Citation) Praecipe (for Record)
Filed in the U.S. District Court, Western Dist. of Washington, Northern Division Jun 1 1915 Frank L. Crosby, Clerk. By Ed M Lakin Deputy
